OL,3,CTwo 24-hour strikes planned by London
OL,4,CUnderground drivers are called off
OL,6,FTwo 24-hour strikes planned by London
OL,7,FUnderground drivers this week have
OL,8,Fbeen called off.
OL,10,FMembers of the Rail, Maritime and
OL,11,FTransport union (RMT) were due to walk
OL,12,Fout at 12 noon tomorrow and again on
OL,13,FThursday in a dispute over the working
OL,14,Fweek.
OL,16,FA union spokesperson said: "At the
OL,17,F11th hour the employer has shifted its
OL,18,Fposition allowing us to further
OL,19,Fexplore our members' concerns around
OL,20,Fthe imposition of new rosters, fatigue
OL,21,Fand safety issues.
OL,26,@xD@\OU
